Tanzanian Deputy Minister for Lands, Angelina Mabula, has said that the demarcation exercise which will commence on March 22,Â  will see the replacement of dilapidated and missing land beacons between Tanzania, Kenya and Uganda borders. There has been strained diplomatic relations between Tanzania and Kenya in the past, over the seizure and sale of cattle belonging to Kenyan Maasai herders that strayed onto Tanzanian land.